Package chat.messages

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientMessage
    The class represents a message the client can send to the server.
    ClientMessageLogin
    This class represents a hello from the client to the server.
    ClientMessageLogout
    This class represents a message the client sends to the server to tell goodbye.
    ClientMessageMessage
    This class represents a message the client send to the server to send a new message.
    DataMessage
    This class represents the content of a message, both used by the server and the client.
    DataMessageInfo  
    DataUser
    This class represents a user in the chat.
    Message
    This class is the core component of a message the client and the server can send an receive.
    ServerMessage
    The class represents a message the server can send to the client.
    ServerMessageConnectionError
    This message is sent by the server when there is a connection error.
    ServerMessageMessages
    This class represents a message the server send to tell the clients all the messages of the chat.
    ServerMessageNewMessage
    This class represents a message the server send to the clients when there is a new message on the chat.
    ServerMessageUsers
    This class represents a message of the server when it's time for the clients to update the user list.
